<head>RACING</head><list type="altnames">
<item>RACES</item></list><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">競賽</item><item xml:lang="och">逐</item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>SPORT of COMPETING with OTHERS IN-RELATION-TO RUNNING OR DRIVING.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The most general word for a speed contest is zhú 逐, which originally means "try to catch up".</p>
<p>2. Yù 御 refers specifically to cart-racing.</p>
<p>3. Chí 馳 refers specifically to horse-racing.</p></div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>競賽</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p></div></div>
